    • setDescription

      public void setDescription(String description)
      Sets a description of this administered object. Corresponds to the description element within administered-object in the JCA connector deployment descriptor.
      Parameters:
      description - a textual description of this administered object
      See Also:
      • Jakarta Connectors 2.0 Specification

    • setJndiName

      public void setJndiName(String jndiName)
      Sets the JNDI name by which this administered object will be registered. Corresponds to the jndi-name element in the JCA connector deployment descriptor.

      The name must be a valid JNDI name.

      Parameters:
      jndiName - the JNDI name for this administered object
      See Also:
      • Jakarta Connectors 2.0 Specification

    • setAdministeredObjectInterface

      public void setAdministeredObjectInterface(String administeredObjectInterface)
      Sets the fully-qualified interface name that this administered object implements. Corresponds to the administered-object-interface element in the JCA connector deployment descriptor.
      Parameters:
      administeredObjectInterface - the administered object interface class name
      See Also:
      • Jakarta Connectors 2.0 Specification

    • setAdministeredObjectClass

      public void setAdministeredObjectClass(String administeredObjectClass)

      Parameters:
      administeredObjectClass - the administered object implementation class name
      See Also:
      • Jakarta Connectors 2.0 Specification
